USA: Repetition is the mother of wisdom
It is funny that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in Afghanistan the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the foolishest.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, expected anxiously, it was shown that it is a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only in the same text is the speech "like in Iraq" used several times, but it also did not hesitate to use the title of Bush's January 2007 declaration for his own statement: "A new way forward".
He was himself, who criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from civil war three years ago, and that was criticized as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences."
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful, so that nothing is spoken of Iraq in the news today.
Bush's reputation did not improve, however, objectively left his successor a situation far more favourable than it might have been expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes the miracle will be repeated.
The camp captains once again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghan operation General Stanley McCristal. He, even in spite of traditional subordinate relationships, submitted undecided gunmen in the White House to a harsh criticism.
He requested 40,000 men to be able to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he cheated on 10,000 military personnel.
He managed to get Europe to promise it another 5,000, although he himself previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic of Obama's whole strategy seems to be its goal, to start withdrawing troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and finalizing this procedure in three years. Obama's entire doctrine generated more questions than the answers he offered.
Many doubt that the increase yields the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq’s society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: it is not possible to trust anyone and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, if they are accustomed to changing their boss every day according to their needs.
The political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. After it will remain the patriarchal tribal relations.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extremely complicated due to confused relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even to establish a state that is "capable of action", a minimum objective of the whole operation, seems very real.
Obama's strategy's horizon shocks for its volunteerism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing of reality, can believe that the military sent to the war to "return home soon," will perform some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of the U.S. defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans are less and less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians don't know, and they don't want to explain to their voters what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and the increased sanctions do not have any effect on the Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek the answers precisely when, according to Obama, America begins the triumphal withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
However, each solution will mean a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that there are three years left for presidential elections and that is why there is still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
