Nesbitt and other paleontologists began an excavation in Ghost Ranch in northern Mexico in 2006.
Sometimes, we have found in one day a dozen dinosaur bones, this is something unprecedented for sediments of the Triasic, reports Randall Irmis member of the Utah Natural History Museum team.
Researchers quickly identified some bones as belonging to a new species.
In the course of the excavation, the remains of five specimens were collected in total.
A finding confirms the theories about the ancient history of dinosaurs
The name "Tawa" comes from the sun god of the Hopi Indians.
For Sterling Nesbitt is an exceptional finding: "Triasic dinosaur fossils are extremely rare, usually only individual fragments are found."
Other experts in dinosaurs do not share such enthusiasm at all.
This finding is not particularly spectacular, but confirms some theories about the ancient history of dinosaurs, for example Martin Sander of the University of Bonn.
According to current opinion, dinosaurs appeared for the first time about 230 million years ago.
But many of the oldest fossils are incomplete, so the classification of these first dinosaurs is quite controversial.
Thus, the experts discuss, for example, when the sauriums were divided into their three most important genealogical lines: the carnivorous teropods among those found in Tyrannosaurus Rex, Velociraptor and also birds, the quadruped sauropods known as "long neck" and their relatives, and the Ornithischia herbivores (sauriums with bird pelvis), which, for example, belong to the species Triceratops and Stegosaurus.
According to Nesbitt's analysis and his colleagues, Tawa foundae is a primitive thermopod.
This shows an interesting combination of primitive and progressive properties, says Nesbitt.
For example, in the skull of Tawa, researchers found signs of air bags, such as those that also own the descendants of the teropods, the birds.
Thanks to the air bags, bird breathing is more efficient than mammals.
In the case of Tawa also found the bones of the spine were evidently filled with air in part.
Tawa is the teropod with older and primitive airbags, says Randall Irmis.
Because the parented line of later giant sauropods also possessed air bags and light bones, it was likely that the common predecessors of both groups had already produced this useful innovation.
At least three migratory waves to North America
Due to the fact that the most primitive dinosaurs so far known lived in South America, researchers suggest that the suris appeared there for the first time.
Thus, the three genealogical lines separated at first and extended from South America by all corners of the earth, which by then still formed a unique earth mass, the Pangea supercontinent.
However, the facts say that the team found the remains of two other less closely related teropods together with Tawa.
The three cannot come down from a single parenter, the researchers argue.
We believe that at least three migratory waves have been given to North America, says Alan Turner of the American Museum of Natural History in New York, co-author of the Science study.
Of course, there are also opponents.
An even older species, Silesaurus, who belongs to a group of brothers from dinosaurs, lived in the current Poland, says the paleontologist of Bonn Martin Sander.
Your opinion could give a distorted image, because simply in South America many fossils of dinosaurs continue to be preserved, while in other continents there is hardly anything to discover.
The question of how dinosaurs evolved from a relatively rare collateral line from reptiles to Mesozoic dominant terrestrial vertebrates remains an enigma.
Meanwhile, in Triasic dinosaurs still shared their vital space with many other reptiles, for example, the ancestors of current crocodiles and pterosauruses and with many other sauris.
Toward the end of the Triastic the dinosaurs expanded all over the world and many new species developed, while the kinship became extinct at the limit of the Triasic towards the Jurassic.
Successive Stories Were Not Eternal
There are two scenarios to explain this change, says Martin Sander.
It could have been given a massive extinction to which dinosaurs survived by chance, but the other reptiles did not.
Or the dinosaurs were better adapted, so they could defeat the opponents in the area.
Successful stories are not always eternal.
150 million years later, a meteorite impact slows the rise of a group of species, which had also evolved in the Triasic and since then had a miserable existence: mammals.
