Internet auction of crash cars
Last October, the Solera group bought Autoonline, an internet platform for the sale of cars such as motorcycles or special damaged vehicles.
The operation involved a disbursement of €59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could be extended to the remaining 15% in the year.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of accessing a huge international market.
This valuation and sales service is directed exclusively to industry professionals, such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, workshops, scrapers and professional sellers who must register before starting operations.
This platform was set up in Germany in 1996 and handles over 650,000 operations across Europe, 500,000 of them in Germany.
Its main markets include Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The website currently has more than 1,500 registered vendors and 4,000 experts.
3,000 daily ads are managed and some 100 new ads are included in the Spanish market every day.
