Workshop budget in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the Audatex company guarantees that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identify the vehicle, seek the replacement, create the budget and generate the budget.
The ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially in order to convince older professionals, who, to a greater or lesser extent, are usually more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 tourism, 109 allterrestrials, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it you need a computer with internet connection.
Once the model has been identified to be repaired by its frame number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the workforce, charges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a review tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the one oriented to the workshop does not include estimated working times.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is EUR 350 per year, which the customer can finance.
Currently Audatex is working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with very good eyes, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it around to see the inside face.
